    "In both cases the value measured from exclusive decay modes (namely B → D * µν µ and B → πµν µ) is smaller than the value obtained from the inclusive B → X c,u µν µ modes [5].",
    "This long standing issue is still unsolved despite the numerous proposed explanations.",
    "2 In addition, there is the so-called Cabibbo-angle anomaly, a ∼ 3σ tension among the determinations of |V us |, together with a deficit from unitarity in the first row of the CKM matrix [7].• Tensions in observables related to the b → s transition.",
    "The branching ratios B(B → Kµ + µ -) and B(B s → ϕµ + µ -) are below the SM estimates.",
    "For the mode B → K * µ + µ - a number of angular observables can be defined, which depend on q 2, the squared dilepton invariant mass [8]."
